A Zimbabwean citizen has reportedly died after collapsed near the Beitbridge border in Limpopo. It's believed she had been on a bus since Monday afternoon. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - A Zimbabwean citizen has reportedly died after collapsing near the Beitbridge border in Limpopo. It is believed she had been on a bus since Monday afternoon. She reportedly complained of fatigue and feeling dizzy, and asked fellow passengers to pray for her. READ: Beitbridge residents want border open Travelers have been trying to cross to Zimbabwe for over a day. Meanwhile, some drivers say they have been stuck in traffic for several days. They say they have no food and water. There has been no official explanation for the delay but some believe it's due to the COVID-19 screening.